text: Cutch or (Kutch/Kachchh) was an Indian Princely state. It was ruled by the Jadeja dynasty from its formation in 1147 until 1948. On May 4, 1948 it merged with India.S. N. Sadasivan, Political and Administrative Integration of Princely States (New Delhi: Mittal Publications, 2005), p. 29 The district is now known as Kutch. == References == Category:Indian princely states Category:Gujarat Category:1147 establishments Category:12th-century establishments in Asia Category:Establishments in India Category:1948 disestablishments in India
title: Kutch (princely state)
